				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No you should be able to see how big the file is even if the header doesn't match the ROM size. But emulators won't be able to run the game properly if the header is wrong.<br /><br />If you are using NROM you can have only one or two PRG banks. Each PRG bank is 16 kB so if your game is bigger than that (minus the 8 kB CHR-ROM) you need two banks. If your PRG-ROM is bigger than 32 kB you need to consider using another mapper.<br />Tokumaru's templates automatically calculates the PRG-ROM start address ($C000 or $8000 for NROM) depending on what you set the PRG_COUNT define to (1 or 2 for NROM).<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Programming_NROM">https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Programming_NROM</a><!-- m --></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

